 CRenderTextureRenderTexture is a generic rendering target. To render things into it, simply construct a render target, call begin on it, call visit on any cocos scenes or objects to render them, and call end. For convenience, render texture adds a sprite as it's display child with the results, so you can simply add the render texture to your scene and treat it like any other CocosNode.  ►CTexture2DTexture2D class. This class allows to easily create OpenGL 2D textures from images, text or raw data. The created Texture2D object will always have power-of-two dimensions. Depending on how you create the Texture2D object, the actual image area of the texture might be smaller than the texture dimensions i.e. "contentSize" != (pixelsWide, pixelsHigh) and (maxS, maxT) != (1.0, 1.0). Be aware that the content of the generated textures will be upside-down!

Supported features: The atlas file can be a PVRTC, PNG or any other format supported by Texture2D Quads can be updated in runtime Quads can be added in runtime Quads can be removed in runtime Quads can be re-ordered in runtime The TextureAtlas capacity can be increased or decreased in runtime OpenGL component: V3F, C4B, T2F.
